Prompt:
When squirrels get together for a party, they like to have cigars. A squirrel party is successful when the number of cigars is between 40 and 60, inclusive. Unless it is the weekend, in which case there is no upper bound on the number of cigars. Return true if the party with the given values is successful, or false otherwise.
public boolean cigarParty(int cigars, boolean isWeekend)
{

}

Response:
Here is a complete implementation of the `cigarParty` method in Java:

```java
public boolean cigarParty(int cigars, boolean isWeekend) {
    if (isWeekend) {
        return cigars >= 40;
    } else {
        return cigars >= 40 && cigars <= 60;
    }
}
```

In this implementation:
- If it is the weekend (isWeekend is true), the party is successful if the number of cigars is greater than or equal to 40.
- If it is not the weekend, the party is successful if the number of cigars is between 40 and 60, inclusive.

You can call this method with the number of cigars and whether it is the weekend to determine if the squirrel party is successful. It will return true if the party is successful, and false otherwise.

