Write a function in Java that implements the following logic: Given 2 int values greater than 0, return whichever value is nearest to 21 without going over. Return 0 if they both go over.
public int blackjack(int a, int b)
{

}

Response:
Here is the implementation of the blackjack function in Java:

```java
public int blackjack(int a, int b) {
    if (a > 21 && b > 21) {
        return 0;
    } else if (a > 21) {
        return b;
    } else if (b > 21) {
        return a;
    } else {
        if (21 - a < 21 - b) {
            return a;
        } else {
            return b;
        }
    }
}
```

This function checks if both numbers are greater than 21 and returns 0 in that case. It then checks if either number is greater than 21 and returns the other number if one is within the limit. Finally, if both numbers are within the limit, it returns the number that is closest to 21 without going over.

